## System Flow (Detailed)

```
Boot / Wake
    │
    ├─ Load saved mode (USB/BLE) from Preferences
    ├─ Init TFT (160×80 landscape), buttons
    ├─ Mount LittleFS, scan *.txt → script list
    ├─ Restore last index from RTC
    └─ Init selected HID (USB or BLE)

        ▼
    Main Screen (Idle, status "Ready")
        │
        ├─ Up/Down      → change script, update display
        ├─ Short Center → confirm mode (status "Run?", 2s timeout)
        │       │
        │       ├─ 2nd Center within 2s → EXECUTE
        │       │       │
        │       │       ├─ (BLE) wait for connection if needed
        │       │       ├─ parse script line by line
        │       │       ├─ send keystrokes via active HID
        │       │       ├─ status "Run…" with spinner
        │       │       └─ finish → "Done!" 1s → back to Idle
        │       │
        │       └─ Up/Down or timeout → cancel back to Idle
        │
        └─ Long Center (1s) → Mode Selection Menu
                │
                ├─ Display: "Select HID Mode:  USB   BLE"
                ├─ Up/Down toggle highlight
                ├─ Short Center confirm
                │       │
                │       ├─ if mode changed → save, reboot
                │       └─ if same → back to Idle
                │
                └─ (no deep sleep during menu)

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ Deep sleep (idle 2 min)                     │
    │ - USB mode: always allowed                  │
    │ - BLE mode: only when disconnected          │
    │ - Save current index to RTC, turn off TFT   │
    │ - Wake on any button → reboot               │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

